==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hammer-beam
<hw>Ham"mer-beam`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦emac⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Gothic
Arch.)</fld> <def>A member of one description of roof truss, called
<xex>hammer-beam truss</xex>, which is so framed as not to have a
tiebeam at the top of the wall. Each principal has two hammer-beams,
which occupy the situation, and to some extent serve the purpose, of a
tiebeam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hammer break</ent>⟦br⟧
